Validating cross-sec interpolation
==================================

For the ATLAS members, get the ATLAS NLO+NLL xsec ROOT file:
  scp lxplus:/afs/cern.ch/atlas/groups/susy/SignalCrossSectionsUncert/ModelSpecific/SignalUncertainties-MSUGRA-mc12.root .
and the SLHA file for each point:
  rsync -avz lxplus:/cvmfs/atlas.cern.ch/repo/sw/Generators/MC12JobOptions/latest/share/DSID156xxx/susy_msugra_*_*_0_10_P_softsusy.slha slha/

We're going to rescale these SLHA files, so let's rename the downloaded SLHA file dir to slha.orig, and make a new empty slha dir:
  mv slha slha.orig
  mkdir slha
(yes, you could just rsync into slha.orig... whatever)

Run this to convert the (corrupted) ATLAS SLHA files to scale = 1 TeV:
  for i in slha.orig/*.slha; do cat $i modsel1TeV.slha.part | softpoint.x leshouches | grep -v "# WARNING" > ${i/.orig/}; done
